    "They give an example where the most commonly occurring form of the French lemma 'président' in the training data, the masculine singular form, becomes even more common after training.",
    "The least common word form of that same lemma, the feminine plural 'présidentes', decreases in frequency and is for some models even completely lost in translation.",
    "In line with the abovementioned research, recent work by Costa-jussà et al. (2022) shows how different architectures trained on the same data exhibit different levels of gender bias.",
